The primary assistant to a teacher is often a co-worker who is delegated to supervise students in and out of class.
Paraprofessional:
In the United States, a paraprofessional is a professional educator who works closely with classroom teachers and students.
Teacher assistant:
A teacher assistant is a certified or uncertified educator who serves as a teaching aide under the supervision of a licensed teacher.
Aide:
An aide provides assistance and support to a teacher, typically working with students one-on-one, in small groups, or in the classroom.
A paraprofessional provides support services including instructional activities that are under the direct supervision of licensed teachers.
In the United States, a teacher assistant is a certified or uncertified educator who works under the direct supervision of a licensed teacher.
A Teaching Assistant in Canada is a qualified teacher who has completed a diploma or degree program in education and is employed by a school where he or she may be used to assist a teacher, supervise activities, mark assignments, and provide support in a classroom. If a Teaching Assistant is assigned to Special Needs students, he or she may have additional training to work with students with physical, language or autism spectrum disorder.
Assistant teachers are required to complete a higher education qualification in primary teaching, after which they can work as Assistant Teachers in Primary Schools in Ireland. Those with a primary teaching qualification but who do not have a higher education qualification will be qualified as Junior or Senior Classroom Assistants depending on the hours they work.
In India, there are several types of teaching assistants like a Trainee Teacher, Trained Graduate Teacher (TGT) and Post-Graduate Teacher (PGT). A Trainee Teacher is in training to become a fully qualified teacher while TGTs and PGTs are fully qualified teachers who assist the teachers at the lower level usually with taking classes in their absence or to support those classes.
